				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/raikonos" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(223989); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=223989&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182943" alt="Raikonos" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=223989)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/raikonos" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(223989); return false;" >Raikonos</a></span> <span class="odate time_1327371430 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">24 Jan 2012 02:17</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1357490">
									

<p>I liked this when I read it, I liked it even more when I read that diary entry, and it got an upvote from me, no question. There are a couple of minor things that bug me though.</p>
<p>First off, the sentence &quot;SCP-745's genetic structure is not carbon based.&quot; I understand why this is here, but the placement of the sentence feels blunt and a little jarring. I'm sure there's a way it could be integrated a little better.</p>
<p>Also, the phrase &quot;the child-like hand prints from SCP-745's front paws&quot; doesn't seem very clinical, at least where it is. I feel like the description of the handprints as child-like should be alongside the other physical attributes. I admit, though, I can't think of another way to get across the creep factor of the handprints.</p>
<p>Like I said, I like this, and 42 other upvotes can't be wrong. These are just a couple of things that jumped out at me.</p>

							</div>

								
					
